{"parse":{"title":"Religion of peace","pageid":8229053,"revid":859267389,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>After the <a href=\"/wiki/September_11_attacks\" title=\"September 11 attacks\">September 11 attacks</a> in 2001, some politicians and activists in the <a href=\"/wiki/Anglophone\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Anglophone\">Anglophone</a> world, such as U.S. President <a href=\"/wiki/George_W._Bush\" title=\"George W. Bush\">George W. Bush</a>, described <a href=\"/wiki/Islam\" title=\"Islam\">Islam</a> as a <b>religion of peace</b> in an effort to distance it from <a href=\"/wiki/Islamic_terrorism\" title=\"Islamic terrorism\">Islamic terrorists</a>.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Usage_of_the_term\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Usage of the term</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Criticism\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Criticism</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#See_also\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">See also</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Usage_of_the_term\">Usage of the term</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Religion_of_peace&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Usage of the term\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>In the past the epithet \"religion of peace and good will towards men\" has been applied to Christianity.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>In the 1960s, <a href=\"/wiki/Malcolm_X\" title=\"Malcolm X\">Malcolm X</a>, acting as a spokesman for the <a href=\"/wiki/Nation_of_Islam\" title=\"Nation of Islam\">Nation of Islam</a>, said on multiple occasions that Islam was a \"religion of peace\".<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Malcolm_X:_Speech_excerpt_from_Los_Angeles_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Malcolm_X:_Speech_excerpt_from_Los_Angeles-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>In 1964, <a href=\"/wiki/Muhammad_Ali\" title=\"Muhammad Ali\">Muhammad Ali</a> used similar phrasing to indicate the relationship between Islam and peace in his justification for why he had joined the <a href=\"/wiki/Nation_of_Islam\" title=\"Nation of Islam\">Nation of Islam</a>, saying, \"You call it Black Muslims, I don't. The real name is Islam. That means peace,\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> as well as \"I believe in Allah and in peace\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>In 1996, the <a href=\"/wiki/Organisation_of_Islamic_Cooperation\" title=\"Organisation of Islamic Cooperation\">Organisation of The Islamic Conference</a> agreed to call for \"pragmatic and constructive steps to counter the negative propaganda against Islam; to remove and rectify misunderstandings; and to present the true image of Islam: the religion of peace and tolerance.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>In September 2001, in the wake of the <a href=\"/wiki/September_11_attacks\" title=\"September 11 attacks\">September 11 attacks</a>, U.S. President <a href=\"/wiki/George_W._Bush\" title=\"George W. Bush\">George W. Bush</a> said: \"The face of terror is not the true faith of Islam.  That's not what Islam is all about.  Islam is peace.  These terrorists don't represent peace. They represent evil and war.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-9\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-10\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup> Some have pointed out that <a href=\"/wiki/Islam#Etymology_and_meaning\" title=\"Islam\">the word \"Islam\"</a> is etymologically related to the <a href=\"/wiki/Arabic\" title=\"Arabic\">Arabic</a> word <a href=\"/wiki/%C5%A0-L-M\" title=\"\u0160-L-M\"><i>sal\u0101m</i></a> meaning \"peace\".<sup id=\"cite_ref-11\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup> This prompted criticism from some quarters<sup id=\"cite_ref-SkepReview_12-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-SkepReview-12\">&#91;12&#93;</a></sup> and a poll of United States <a href=\"/wiki/Evangelical\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Evangelical\">Evangelical</a> <a href=\"/wiki/Protestant\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Protestant\">Protestant</a> leaders taken in 2002 revealed that only 10% agreed with Bush that Islam was synonymous with peace.<sup id=\"cite_ref-13\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-13\">&#91;13&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p><a href=\"/wiki/Mahathir_bin_Mohamad\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Mahathir bin Mohamad\">Mahathir bin Mohamad</a>, the former Prime Minister of <a href=\"/wiki/Malaysia\" title=\"Malaysia\">Malaysia</a> said in 2002, \"Islam, as I said, is a religion of peace. However through the centuries, deviations from the true teachings of Islam take place. And so [people who call themselves] \"Muslims\" kill despite the injunction of their religion against killing especially of innocent people.<sup id=\"cite_ref-MALAY_14-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-MALAY-14\">&#91;14&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p><a href=\"/wiki/Dalil_Boubakeur\" title=\"Dalil Boubakeur\">Dalil Boubakeur</a>, <i><a href=\"/wiki/Mufti\" title=\"Mufti\">mufti</a></i> of the <a href=\"/wiki/Paris_Mosque\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Paris Mosque\">Paris Mosque</a>, said in 2006, \"<a href=\"/wiki/Muhammed\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Muhammed\">The prophet</a> did not found a terrorist religion, but a religion of peace.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-15\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-15\">&#91;15&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Following the <a href=\"/wiki/2015_San_Bernardino_attack\" title=\"2015 San Bernardino attack\">2015 San Bernardino attack</a>, US President <a href=\"/wiki/Barack_Obama\" title=\"Barack Obama\">Barack Obama</a> used the term, as part of his efforts to counter a perceived anti-Muslim bias, in an address following the attack,<sup id=\"cite_ref-16\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-16\">&#91;16&#93;</a></sup> and in his first visit to a US mosque.<sup id=\"cite_ref-17\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-17\">&#91;17&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Criticism\">Criticism</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Religion_of_peace&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Criticism\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:2012_Sydney_protest.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/73/2012_Sydney_protest.jpg/220px-2012_Sydney_protest.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"147\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/73/2012_Sydney_protest.jpg/330px-2012_Sydney_protest.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/73/2012_Sydney_protest.jpg/440px-2012_Sydney_protest.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"2048\" data-file-height=\"1365\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:2012_Sydney_protest.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Muslim protesters carry signs reading \"<a href=\"/wiki/Decapitation\" title=\"Decapitation\">Behead</a> all those who insult the <a href=\"/wiki/Muhammad\" title=\"Muhammad\">Prophet</a>\" and \"Our dead are in Paradise. Your dead are in HELL!\"</div></div></div>\n<p><a href=\"/wiki/Sherman_Jackson\" title=\"Sherman Jackson\">Sherman Jackson</a> says that the expression does not imply a rejection of <a href=\"/wiki/Jihad\" title=\"Jihad\">the laws of Jihad</a>, but rather the idea that <a href=\"/wiki/Islam\" title=\"Islam\">Islam</a> desires a \"a state of permanent, peaceful coexistence with other nations and peoples who are not Muslims\".<sup id=\"cite_ref-18\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-18\">&#91;18&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The term \"The Religion of Peace\" is used mockingly by <a href=\"/wiki/Criticism_of_Islam\" title=\"Criticism of Islam\">critics of Islam</a>, such as right-wing commentator <a href=\"/wiki/Ann_Coulter\" title=\"Ann Coulter\">Ann Coulter</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-counterp_19-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-counterp-19\">&#91;19&#93;</a></sup> Philosopher and <a href=\"/wiki/New_Atheism\" title=\"New Atheism\">New Atheist</a> writer <a href=\"/wiki/Sam_Harris\" title=\"Sam Harris\">Sam Harris</a> wrote, \"The position of the Muslim community in the face of all provocations seems to be: Islam is a religion of peace, and if you say that it isn't, we will kill you.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-20\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-20\">&#91;20&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>When asked by reporters in 2005 if Islam was a religion of peace, <a href=\"/wiki/Pope_Benedict_XVI\" title=\"Pope Benedict XVI\">Pope Benedict XVI</a> stated that some elements of Islam can favor peace, but it also has other elements. \n<sup id=\"cite_ref-21\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-21\">&#91;21&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p><a href=\"/wiki/Islamist\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Islamist\">Islamist</a> <a href=\"/wiki/Sayyid_Qutb\" title=\"Sayyid Qutb\">Sayyid Qutb</a> wrote that Islam is the religion of peace in the sense of submitting all of mankind to <a href=\"/wiki/Allah\" title=\"Allah\">Allah</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-22\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-22\">&#91;22&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>On May 13, 2015, <a href=\"/wiki/Islamic_State_of_Iraq_and_the_Levant\" title=\"Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant\">ISIL</a> released an audio message by <a href=\"/wiki/Abu_Bakr_al-Baghdadi\" title=\"Abu Bakr al-Baghdadi\">Abu Bakr al-Baghdadi</a>, who asserted that Islam is not a religion of peace, but rather the religion of fighting.\n<sup id=\"cite_ref-23\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-23\">&#91;23&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Following the <a href=\"/wiki/2017_Barcelona_attacks\" title=\"2017 Barcelona attacks\">2017 Barcelona attacks</a>, the cover of <i><a href=\"/wiki/Charlie_Hebdo\" title=\"Charlie Hebdo\">Charlie Hebdo</a></i> ran with an image of a van driving away from bloodied victims with the caption \"Islam, religion of peace... Eternal\".<sup id=\"cite_ref-24\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-24\">&#91;24&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-25\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-25\">&#91;25&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-26\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-26\">&#91;26&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Religion_of_peace&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div role=\"navigation\" aria-label=\"Portals\" class=\"noprint portal plainlist tright\" style=\"margin:0.5em 0 0.5em 1em;border:solid #aaa 1px\">\n<ul style=\"display:table;box-sizing:border-box;padding:0.1em;max-width:175px;background:#f9f9f9;font-size:85%;line-height:110%;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold\">\n<li style=\"display:table-row\"><span style=\"display:table-cell;padding:0.2em;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4e/Allah-green.svg/27px-Allah-green.svg.png\" width=\"27\" height=\"28\" class=\"noviewer\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4e/Allah-green.svg/40px-Allah-green.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4e/Allah-green.svg/54px-Allah-green.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"206\" data-file-height=\"215\" /></span><span style=\"display:table-cell;padding:0.2em 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em;vertical-align:middle\"><a href=\"/wiki/Portal:Islam\" title=\"Portal:Islam\">Islam portal</a></span></li></ul></div>\n<table role=\"presentation\" class=\"mbox-small plainlinks sistersitebox\" style=\"background-color:#f9f9f9;border:1px solid #aaa;color:#000\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<td class=\"mbox-image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/fa/Wikiquote-logo.svg/34px-Wikiquote-logo.svg.png\" width=\"34\" height=\"40\" class=\"noviewer\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/fa/Wikiquote-logo.svg/51px-Wikiquote-logo.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/fa/Wikiquote-logo.svg/68px-Wikiquote-logo.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"300\" data-file-height=\"355\" /></td>\n<td class=\"mbox-text plainlist\">Wikiquote has quotations related to: <i><b><a href=\"https://en.wikiquote.org/wiki/Special:Search/Religion_of_peace\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"q:Special:Search/Religion of peace\">Religion of peace</a></b></i></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Islam_and_other_religions\" title=\"Islam and other religions\">Islam and other religions</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Peace_in_Islamic_philosophy\" title=\"Peace in Islamic philosophy\">Peace in Islamic philosophy</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Islam_and_violence\" title=\"Islam and violence\">Islam and violence</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Pacifism_in_Islam\" title=\"Pacifism in Islam\">Pacifism in Islam</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Islamic_terrorism\" title=\"Islamic terrorism\">Islamic terrorism</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Religion_of_peace&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap mw-references-columns\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i>Defensive War not Inconsistent with a Religion of Peace</i>, a sermon, Seeley, Jackson, &amp; Halliday, 1860, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=al1u2i6q5aQC&amp;pg=PA11\">p. 11</a> Quote: \"While however it is manifest and unquestionable that Christianity is emphatically a religion of peace and good will towards men &#8212; men of all countries and of all climes  &#8212; it is assuredly not a religion of absolute and passive non-resistance.\"</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\">Nessen, Stephen. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.wnyc.org/story/87636-remembering-malcolm-x-rare-interviews-and-audio/\">\"Remembering Malcolm X: Rare Interviews and Audio\"</a>. <i>WNYC - New York Public Radio</i>. WNYC - New York Public Radio<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">1 April</span> 2018</span>. <q>The Honorable Elijah Muhammad teaches us the religion of Islam, which is a religion of peace.</q></cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=WNYC+-+New+York+Public+Radio&amp;rft.atitle=Remembering+Malcolm+X%3A+Rare+Interviews+and+Audio&amp;rft.aulast=Nessen&amp;rft.aufirst=Stephen&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wnyc.org%2Fstory%2F87636-remembering-malcolm-x-rare-interviews-and-audio%2F&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AReligion+of+peace\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Malcolm_X:_Speech_excerpt_from_Los_Angeles-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-Malcolm_X:_Speech_excerpt_from_Los_Angeles_3-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation audio-visual\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://search.alexanderstreet.com/view/2787248\"><i>Malcolm X: Speech excerpt from Los Angeles</i></a> (speech). Educational Video Group. 1962<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">1 April</span> 2018</span>  &#8211; via <a href=\"/wiki/Alexander_Street\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Alexander Street\">Alexander Street</a>. <span style=\"font-size:90%; color:#555\">(Subscription required (<span title=\"The site requires a paid subscription to access this page.\" style=\"border-bottom:1px dotted;cursor:help\">help</span>))</span>. <q>They also say that, uh, the Honorable Elijah Muhammad was a draft dodger. No he wasn't. He just refused to go to the army because he was a man of peace. He was a minister of a religion of peace. He was teaching peace, so he outright refused to go to the army.</q></cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Malcolm+X%3A+Speech+excerpt+from+Los+Angeles&amp;rft.pub=Educational+Video+Group&amp;rft.date=1962&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fsearch.alexanderstreet.com%2Fview%2F2787248&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AReligion+of+peace\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/books/98/10/25/specials/ali-islam.html\">\"Clay Says He Has Adopted Islam Religion and Regards It as Way to Peace\"</a>. New York Times. February 28, 1964.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Clay+Says+He+Has+Adopted+Islam+Religion+and+Regards+It+as+Way+to+Peace&amp;rft.pub=New+York+Times&amp;rft.date=1964-02-28&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2Fbooks%2F98%2F10%2F25%2Fspecials%2Fali-islam.html&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AReligion+of+peace\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-5\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\">Gass, Henry (10 June 2016). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.csmonitor.com/USA/Society/2016/0610/The-religious-journey-of-Muhammad-Ali-ambassador-of-Islam\">\"The religious journey of Muhammad Ali, 'ambassador' of Islam\"</a>. <i>www.csmonitor.com</i>. The Christian Science Monitor<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">1 April</span> 2018</span>. <q>As he adopted a more mainstream interpretation of Islam, he maintained his overriding principle that it was a religion of peace.  \"I believe in Allah and in peace,\" he said after announcing his conversion in 1964.</q></cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=www.csmonitor.com&amp;rft.atitle=The+religious+journey+of+Muhammad+Ali%2C+%27ambassador%27+of+Islam&amp;rft.date=2016-06-10&amp;rft.aulast=Gass&amp;rft.aufirst=Henry&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.csmonitor.com%2FUSA%2FSociety%2F2016%2F0610%2FThe-religious-journey-of-Muhammad-Ali-ambassador-of-Islam&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AReligion+of+peace\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-6\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\">Littman, David. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.meforum.org/477/islamism-grows-stronger-at-the-united-nations\">\"Islamism Grows Stronger at the United Nations\"</a>. The Middle East Quarterly.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Islamism+Grows+Stronger+at+the+United+Nations&amp;rft.pub=The+Middle+East+Quarterly&amp;rft.aulast=Littman&amp;rft.aufirst=David&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.meforum.org%2F477%2Fislamism-grows-stronger-at-the-united-nations&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AReligion+of+peace\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-7\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-7\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/academia.edu.documents/27669652/merskin_the_construction.pdf?AWSAccessKeyId=AKIAIWOWYYGZ2Y53UL3A&amp;Expires=1514452963&amp;Signature=rSiQXAH2iIoRvEEzqkdlNYMIwjw%3D&amp;response-content-disposition=inline%3B%20filename%3DThe_construction_of_Arabs_as_enemies_Pos.pdf\">Merskin, Debra. \"The construction of Arabs as enemies: Post-September 11 discourse of George W. Bush.\" Mass Communication &amp; Society 7.2 (2004): 157-175.</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-8\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-8\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.researchgate.net/profile/Corwin_Smidt/publication/238412257_Religion_and_American_Attitudes_Toward_Islam_and_an_Invasion_of_Iraq/links/5473a71d0cf2778985abb8e1.pdf\">Smidt, Corwin E. \"Religion and American attitudes toward Islam and an invasion of Iraq.\" Sociology of Religion 66.3 (2005): 243-261.</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-9\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-9\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.researchgate.net/profile/Bruce_Lincoln2/publication/297176917_Bush%27s_God_Talk/links/5864ec1708ae6eb871adacdf/Bushs-God-Talk.pdf\">Lincoln, Bruce. \"Bush\u2019s God Talk.\" Political Theologies: Public Religions in a Post-Secular World (2006): 275.</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-10\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-10\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation pressrelease\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://georgewbush-whitehouse.archives.gov/news/releases/2001/09/20010917-11.html\">\"<span style=\"padding-left:0.2em;\">\"</span>Islam is Peace\" Says President\"</a> (Press release). Office of the Press Secretary. 2001-09-17<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2007-11-22</span></span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=%22Islam+is+Peace%22+Says+President&amp;rft.pub=Office+of+the+Press+Secretary&amp;rft.date=2001-09-17&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fgeorgewbush-whitehouse.archives.gov%2Fnews%2Freleases%2F2001%2F09%2F20010917-11.html&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AReligion+of+peace\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-11\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-11\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation news\">Armstrong, Karen (23 September 2001). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://content.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,175987,00.html\">\"The True, Peaceful Face Of Islam\"</a>. <i>Time</i><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">22 July</span> 2017</span>. <q>The very word Islam, which means \"surrender,\" is related to the Arabic salam, or peace.</q></cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Time&amp;rft.atitle=The+True%2C+Peaceful+Face+Of+Islam&amp;rft.date=2001-09-23&amp;rft.aulast=Armstrong&amp;rft.aufirst=Karen&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fcontent.time.com%2Ftime%2Fmagazine%2Farticle%2F0%2C9171%2C175987%2C00.html&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AReligion+of+peace\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-SkepReview-12\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-SkepReview_12-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\">Till, Farrell (November 2001). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.webcitation.org/66GYIvd3A?url=http://www.theskepticalreview.com/tsrmag/016front.html\">\"The Real Culprit\"</a>. The Skeptical Review. Archived from <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.infidels.org/library/magazines/tsr/2001/6/016front.html\">the original</a> on 2012-03-18<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2007-11-22</span></span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=The+Real+Culprit&amp;rft.pub=The+Skeptical+Review&amp;rft.date=2001-11&amp;rft.aulast=Till&amp;rft.aufirst=Farrell&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.infidels.org%2Flibrary%2Fmagazines%2Ftsr%2F2001%2F6%2F016front.html&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AReligion+of+peace\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-13\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-13\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\">Green, John (2003-04-07). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.beliefnet.com/story/124/story_12447_1.html\">\"Evangelical Views of Islam\"</a>. EPPC and beliefnet<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2007-11-22</span></span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Evangelical+Views+of+Islam&amp;rft.pub=EPPC+and+beliefnet&amp;rft.date=2003-04-07&amp;rft.aulast=Green&amp;rft.aufirst=John&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.beliefnet.com%2Fstory%2F124%2Fstory_12447_1.html&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AReligion+of+peace\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-MALAY-14\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-MALAY_14-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://asiasociety.org/islam-terrorism-and-malaysias-response?page=0,1\">\"Islam, Terrorism, and Malaysia's Response (page 2)\"</a>. <i>Asia Society</i>. 4 February 2002.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=Asia+Society&amp;rft.atitle=Islam%2C+Terrorism%2C+and+Malaysia%27s+Response+%28page+2%29&amp;rft.date=2002-02-04&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fasiasociety.org%2Fislam-terrorism-and-malaysias-response%3Fpage%3D0%2C1&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AReligion+of+peace\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-15\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-15\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20060204165912/http://www.iht.com/articles/2006/02/02/news/toon.php\">\"Prophet cartoons enraging Muslims\"</a>. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Herald_Tribune\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"International Herald Tribune\">International Herald Tribune</a>. 2 February 2006. Archived from <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.iht.com/articles/2006/02/02/news/toon.php\">the original</a> on 4 February 2006<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2007-11-22</span></span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Prophet+cartoons+enraging+Muslims&amp;rft.pub=International+Herald+Tribune&amp;rft.date=2006-02-02&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.iht.com%2Farticles%2F2006%2F02%2F02%2Fnews%2Ftoon.php&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AReligion+of+peace\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-16\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-16\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/2015/12/23/us/us-muslims-begin-to-publicly-confront-questions-on-islam-and-violence.html?mcubz=0\">U.S. Muslims Reach Out to Address Questions on Islam and Violence</a>, New York Times, Laurie Goodstein, 22 Dec 2015</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-17\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-17\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/2016/02/04/us/politics/obama-muslims-baltimore-mosque.html?mcubz=0\">Obama, in Mosque Visit, Denounces Anti-Muslim Bias</a>, New York Times, Gardiner Harris, 3 Feb 2016</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-18\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-18\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation journal\">Jackson, Sherman (December 2001). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.lamppostproductions.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/JIHAD_MOD_WLD.pdf\">\"Jihad and the Modern World\"</a> <span style=\"font-size:85%;\">(PDF)</span><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2017-09-10</span></span>. <q>\"... Religion of peace\" connotes, rather, that Islam can countenance a state of permanent, peaceful coexistence with other nations and peoples who are not Muslims. In other words, contrary to the belief that Islam can only accept a world that is entirely populated by Muslims</q></cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Jihad+and+the+Modern+World&amp;rft.date=2001-12&amp;rft.aulast=Jackson&amp;rft.aufirst=Sherman&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.lamppostproductions.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2011%2F01%2FJIHAD_MOD_WLD.pdf&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AReligion+of+peace\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-counterp-19\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-counterp_19-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\">Siddiqi, Imraan (5 June 2003). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20030613090741/http://counterpunch.org/siddiqi06052003.html\">\"Ann Coulter's Foul Mouth: The Blond Hate Machine\"</a>. Counterpunch. Archived from <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.counterpunch.org/siddiqi06052003.html\">the original</a> on 13 June 2003<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2007-11-22</span></span>. <q>Ann on the other hand, apparently missed this Sunday school lesson, and continues to ridicule Islam sarcastically as the \"religion of peace\" whenever a negative story arises within the Muslim world.</q></cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Ann+Coulter%27s+Foul+Mouth%3A+The+Blond+Hate+Machine&amp;rft.pub=Counterpunch&amp;rft.date=2003-06-05&amp;rft.aulast=Siddiqi&amp;rft.aufirst=Imraan&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.counterpunch.org%2Fsiddiqi06052003.html&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AReligion+of+peace\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-20\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-20\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\">Harris, Sam (5 May 2008). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.huffingtonpost.com/sam-harris/losing-our-spines-to-save_b_100132.html\">\"Losing Our Spines to Save Our Necks\"</a>. <i>Huffingtonpost.com</i><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">19 March</span> 2011</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=Huffingtonpost.com&amp;rft.atitle=Losing+Our+Spines+to+Save+Our+Necks&amp;rft.date=2008-05-05&amp;rft.aulast=Harris&amp;rft.aufirst=Sam&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.huffingtonpost.com%2Fsam-harris%2Flosing-our-spines-to-save_b_100132.html&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AReligion+of+peace\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span> (updated 25 May 2011)</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-21\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-21\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">\n<cite class=\"citation news\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.catholicnewsagency.com/news/pope_says_terror_attacks_cannot_be_defined_as_antichristian/\">\"Pope says terror attacks cannot be defined as anti-Christian\"</a>. <i>Catholic News Agency</i>. 2005-07-25<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2016-02-25</span></span>. <q>I would not like to use big words to apply generic labels. It certainly contains elements that can favor peace, it also has other elements: we must always seek the best elements.</q></cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Catholic+News+Agency&amp;rft.atitle=Pope+says+terror+attacks+cannot+be+defined+as+anti-Christian&amp;rft.date=2005-07-25&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.catholicnewsagency.com%2Fnews%2Fpope_says_terror_attacks_cannot_be_defined_as_antichristian%2F&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AReligion+of+peace\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-22\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-22\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\"><a href=\"/wiki/Sayyid_Qutb\" title=\"Sayyid Qutb\">Qutb, Sayyid</a>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20061017053855/http://www.islamqa.com/index.php?ref=43087&amp;ln=eng\"><i>Fiqh al-Da'wah</i></a>. <i>Fiqh al-Da'wah</i>. <a href=\"/wiki/IslamQA\" title=\"IslamQA\">IslamQA</a>. pp.&#160;217\u2013222. Archived from <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.islamqa.com/index.php?ref=43087&amp;ln=eng\">the original</a> on 2006-10-17<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2007-11-22</span></span>. <q>The defeatists should fear Allah lest they distort this religion and cause it to become weak on the basis of the claim that it is a religion of peace. Yes, it is the religion of peace but in the sense of saving all of mankind from worshiping anything other than Allah and submitting all of mankind to the rule of Allah.</q></cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Fiqh+al-Da%27wah&amp;rft.pages=217-222&amp;rft.pub=IslamQA&amp;rft.aulast=Qutb&amp;rft.aufirst=Sayyid&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.islamqa.com%2Findex.php%3Fref%3D43087%26ln%3Deng&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AReligion+of+peace\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-23\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-23\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation news\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20150517001734/http://www.christianpost.com/news/isis-caliph-baghdadi-in-new-audio-message-islam-was-never-a-religion-of-peace-our-jihad-is-the-war-of-all-muslims-139166/\">\"ISIS Caliph Baghdadi in New Audio Message: 'Islam Was Never a Religion of Peace,' Our Jihad Is 'The War of All Muslims<span style=\"padding-right:0.2em;\">'</span>\"</a>. <i>The Christian Post</i>. 2015-05-15. Archived from <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.christianpost.com/news/isis-caliph-baghdadi-in-new-audio-message-islam-was-never-a-religion-of-peace-our-jihad-is-the-war-of-all-muslims-139166/\">the original</a> on 2015-05-17<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2015-05-16</span></span>. <q>Islam was never a religion of peace. Islam is the religion of fighting. No one should believe that the war that we are waging is the war of the Islamic State. It is the war of all Muslims, but the Islamic State is spearheading it. It is the war of Muslims against infidels. O Muslims, go to war everywhere. It is the duty of every Muslim.</q></cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=The+Christian+Post&amp;rft.atitle=ISIS+Caliph+Baghdadi+in+New+Audio+Message%3A+%27Islam+Was+Never+a+Religion+of+Peace%2C%27+Our+Jihad+Is+%27The+War+of+All+Muslims%27&amp;rft.date=2015-05-15&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.christianpost.com%2Fnews%2Fisis-caliph-baghdadi-in-new-audio-message-islam-was-never-a-religion-of-peace-our-jihad-is-the-war-of-all-muslims-139166%2F&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AReligion+of+peace\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-24\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-24\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.ilgiornale.it/news/cronache/islam-religione-pace-charlie-sfida-i-musulmani-1433273.html\">\"Islam religione di pace\" Charlie sfida i musulmani</a>, Il Giornale, 23 August 2017</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-25\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-25\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.publico.es/sociedad/charlie-hebdo-dedica-portada-atentado-ramblas-barcelona.html\">'Charlie Hebdo' dedica su portada al atentado de Las Ramblas de Barcelona</a>, Publico, 23 August 2017</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-26\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-26\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.newsweek.com/barcelona-attack-charlie-hebdo-publishes-controversial-front-cover-about-islam-653959\">BARCELONA ATTACK: CHARLIE HEBDO PUBLISHES CONTROVERSIAL ANTI-ISLAM COVER ART</a>, Newsweek, Jack Moore, 23 August 2017</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nParsed by mw2238\nCached time: 20180912221634\nCache expiry: 1900800\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.216 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.249 seconds\nPreprocessor visi